Network-Issues/Slow-Internet.md
# Slow Internet on Company Wi-Fi

## Symptoms
- Pages load slowly
- Video/Teams lag
- Speedtest is lower than expected

## Possible Causes
- Weak Wi-Fi signal
- High bandwidth use
- Outdated drivers
- Interference
- Network congestion

## Troubleshooting Steps
1. Check Wi-Fi signal strength
2. Restart Wi-Fi adapter
3. Run speedtest
4. Try another network (hotspot)
5. Update network drivers
6. Test wired connection
7. Reboot laptop
8. Check if issue affects others

## Root Cause Examples
- Low signal coverage
- Driver compatibility issue
- Faulty router/AP
- Too many users on Wi-Fi

## Resolution
- Move closer to access point
- Update drivers
- Switch frequency band (2.4/5GHz)
- Escalate to networking team if latency >100ms

## User Communication
“Your device is experiencing weak Wi-Fi strength. I have optimized your connection and updated your drivers. Please let me know if performance improves.”

Security-and-MFA/MFA-Push-Not-Working.md
# MFA Push Notification Not Working

## Symptoms
- User does not receive MFA push notification

## Possible Causes
- Notifications disabled
- Authenticator app outdated
- Battery optimization blocking app
- Device not enrolled correctly

## Troubleshooting Steps
1. Confirm correct device registered
2. Ask user to open Authenticator manually
3. Check notification settings
4. Disable battery optimization
5. Update Authenticator app
6. Try verification code instead
7. Re-register MFA if needed

## Resolution
- Reactivated MFA app
- Updated authentication method
- Verified login security

## Security Note
Always verify user identity before changes.

End-User-Guides/Reset-Your-Password.md
# How To Reset Your Password (Simple Guide)

## Step 1
Go to the Password Reset Portal.

## Step 2
Enter your username or email.

## Step 3
Verify your identity (SMS / Email / MFA).

## Step 4
Create a new password.

✔ Tip: Use at least 12 characters  
✔ Avoid using old passwords  
✔ Never share your password

If you still cannot log in, contact IT Support.
